(IACBE) accredited MBA programmes (2017)\n* \u2018Best Training Institute Award\u2019 for the Port and Shipping Management programme at International SHIPTEK conference held in Dubai in 2016\n* Five stars for employability and campus facilities and four stars for teaching methodologies by globally acclaimed QS Ratings in 2016\n* \u2018University with Best Industry Academic Partnership\u2019 by [[India Today (TV channel)|India Today TV]]-Higher Education Excellence Awards\n* \u2018India\u2019s Best University for Innovation and Value based Education\u2019 by the Corporate Council for Leadership & Awareness (CCLA)\n\n== Life at UPES ==\n\n=== '''Student Chapter at UPES''' ===\nStudent Chapters provide unique opportunities for networking, mentoring and bonding over common interests. They provide support both within the student community and to local communities outside the institution. Student Chapters are intended to provide a platform through which students may share their special concerns and run programs for students and other members of the community with an interest in information science.\n\nUnder the '''School of Engineering'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-engineering|title=School of Engineering : Best School For Engineering in India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>, the student chapters are-\n\n* ASHRAE<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/ashraeupes/|title=ASHRAE UPES (@ashraeupes) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[American Society of Heating, Refrigerating and Air Conditioning Engineers|American Society of Heating, Refrigerating and Air-Conditioning Engineers]])\n* ASME<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upesasme/|title=UPES ASME Student Section (@upesasme) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[American Society of Mechanical Engineers]])\n* IEEE<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upes.ieee/|title=UPES IEEE (@upes.ieee) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers|The Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers]]) - IEEE student branch provides a platform for the students to enhance their leadership qualities and technical skills. It organises the various technical and non-technical activities across every year at UPES. Apart from these activities, IEEE student branch conducts its Technical Fest ELECTRA<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/ieeeelectra/|title=UPES IEEE-eLECTRA (@ieeeelectra) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> under the banner of Electrical and Electronics Engineering Department.\n\n* UPES FIPI Student Chapter <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upes_fipi/|title=UPES FIPI Student Chapter (@upes_fipi) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>(Federation of Indian Petroleum Industry) - Students are provided with a series of events and workshops for better learning in the field of Petroleum & Chemical Engineering. UPES FIPI Student Chapter was the first student chapter to be set up in UPES.\n\n* SPE<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upes_spesc/|title=UPES SPE SC (@upes_spesc) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[Society of Petroleum Engineers]])- SPE stands for Society of Petroleum Engineers. SPE is an international not-for-profit organization that works for the enhancement and development of the entire [[Oil and gas industry in India|Oil and Gas industry]]. It is a platform that connects everyone related to Oil and Gas industry, students and professionals alike. [https://www.instagram.com/upes_spesc/ UPES SPE Student Chapter] was set up in 2009 and has been substantiating the mission of SPE International- to collect, disseminate and exchange technical knowledge pertaining to the Energy sector. The Chapter has more than thousand members and provides light to students not only [[Petroleum]] and [[Earth science|Earth Sciences]] but also from [[Chemical engineering|Chemical Engineering]] and [[Computer science|Computer Science]]s. The Chapter has been bridging the gap between Academia and Industry through various events, conferences, and other activities, at national level, regional level and internationally.\n\n* AAPG<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upesaapg/|title=UPES AAPG Student Chapter (@upesaapg) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[American Association of Petroleum Geologists|American Association of Petroleum Geologist]])- It is one of the eight active AAPG student chapters in India. The annual event \u2018Crust\u2019 comprises guest lectures, workshop and trainings.\n\n* SEG<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upes_seg/|title=UPES SEG Student Chapter (@upes_seg) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[Society of Exploration Geophysicists|Society of Explorations Geophysicists]])- Providing a multitude of opportunities to its members, the society has been serving them with events, information and networking since its inception in 2009. The UPES student chapter is affiliated to the SEG society and has been dedicated to the field of [[Geology]] and education of Exploration [[Geophysics|Geophysicists]].\n\n* IIChE<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/iiche_upes/|title=IIChE UPES Student Chapter (@iiche_upes) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[Indian Institute of Chemical Engineers]])- The primary objective of the Students\u2019 Chapter is to promote among students of [[Chemical engineering|Chemical Engineering]] a feeling of fraternity and brotherhood and to complement the objectives and activities of the institute. The activities of the Students\u2019 Chapter includes lectures, film shows and video shows related to the Chemical Engineering education and profession.\n\n* FSAI (Fire and Security Association of India)- FSAI is a non-profit organisation established in 2002 representing the Fire Protection, Life Safety, Security, Building Automation, Loss Prevention and Risk Management domains.\n\n* ASSP ([[American Society of Safety Professionals|American Society of Safety Professional]])- ASSP student section of UPES is the first student section of ASSP in India. At present it consists of 150 student members. The objective of the section is to promote the advancement of the safety profession and safety education and to foster the professional well-being and development of its members within the campus and community.\n\n* GreenUp- Green up is functioning under the [[Department of Health Safety and Environment]] of University of Petroleum & Energy Studies, Dehradun. Green up is a cause against environmental peril. In UPES, Green Up has always strived for extending various initiations taken by [[Government of India|Indian government]] by organising campaigns and events that commence nationally. Green Up is focuses on mobilising and empowering communities to participate in preserving nature and preventing environmental degradation, thereby improving the quality and maintaining the ingenuity and integrity of nature.\n\n* Aero Club<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/aeroclubupes/|title=AeroClub (@aeroclubupes) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> - The club organises paper plane event, Mayday, [[water rocket]] and other events like Aerokriti. In Aerokriti, winners get value certificates and all the participants receive participation certificates. The club releases \u2018Aerogram\u2019- the official college magazine. Aerogram writes out all the achievements, space calendar, space facts of a month and releases by the end of every month.\n\n* Infinity Space Club<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/infinity_space_club/|title=InfinitySpaceClub (@infinity_space_club) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> (ISC) is a student club that functions under Department of [[Aerospace engineering|Aerospace Engineering]], University of Petroleum and Energy Studies. The ISC is a student activity club, which aims at providing technical knowledge to all of its members through a series of workshops, observation nights and guest lectures. Events are conducted regularly which aim at analyzing the current trends in [[Space technology|Space Technology]].\n\n* ASCE<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/asce.upes/|title=ASCE UPES (@asce.upes) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> - [[American Society of Civil Engineers]]\n* UPES-AEE<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upes.aee/|title=UPES - AEE (@upes.aee) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[Association of Energy Engineers]])- This is the newest Student Chapter in UPES.\n\n\nUnder the '''School of Computer Science'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-computer-science|title=School of Computer Science {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>, the student chapters are-\n\n* CSA<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upescsa/|title=UPES CSA (@upescsa) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[Cloud Security Alliance]]) - Cloud is the future technology of Computer Science which is growing at a fast pace. It resolves the storage as well as computational power problems of every individual and hence is being adopted in every domain. Despite all this, the primary obstacle faced by cloud is the security issue. People all around the globe do not consider it to be secure. This society works to eradicate this problem in collaboration with \u2018Cloud Security Alliance\u2019 which is not only an international chapter, but also an international organisation dealing with cloud security and its functionality. This chapter educates the students of UPES about cloud.\n* CSI<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upescsi/|title=UPES CSI STUDENT CHAPTER (@upescsi) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[Computer Society of India]]) ISSA Dehradun Chapter- With the burning desire and enthusiasm to be different from the crowd, UPES-CSI Student Chapter was established in the year 2010 and is one of the most active chapters of UPES. The Society focuses on scientific and educational programs directed towards the development of theory and practice of [[Computer science|Computer Science and Technology]]. The Chapter organizes several technical and fun events, seminars, conferences, regional as well as national student conventions. The chapter strives to create a quintessential example of an ideal workplace by evoking participation of 600+ members in its annual national convention \u2013 YUGMAK. Along with various technical and non-technical competitions, UPES-CSI as a student chapter also carries out its duties towards the society through various CSR activities organised every year.\n* UPES ACM<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upesacm/|title=UPES ACM Student Chapter (@upesacm) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> - [[Association for Computing Machinery]]- International chapter based out of [[New York City|New York]]-[[United States|USA]], with the focus to sensitise students in the area of basic computing.\n* [[CodeChef|UPES-CODE CHEF]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/codechefupes/|title=Codechef UPES Campus Chapter (@codechefupes) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n* Smart Analyzers<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/smartanalyzers/|title=Smart Analyzers (@smartanalyzers) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n* HYPERVISION<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upeshypervision/|title=UPES Hypervision (@upeshypervision) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> Informatics Club\n* Cyber Sentinel<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/cybersentinelupes/|title=Cyber Sentinel (@cybersentinelupes) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n\n\nUnder the '''School of Design'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-design|title=School of Design : Best Design University in Dehradun, India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>, the student chapters are-\n\n* Sketching Club\n* UWUTAKU<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/teamuwutaku/|title=UWUTAKU (@teamuwutaku) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n* Film Club\n\n\nUnder the '''School of Business'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-business|title=School of Business Management : Business School For MBA & Economics - UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>, the student chapters are-\n\n* International Affairs    \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0\n* Events\n* Academic & Research \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \