e to one counseling. Difficulties in academics and learning are dealt with through faculty mentors. UPES is among one of the few universities that understand the student's need for a friend, guide, role model and mentor. The department of Student Engagement and Experience works closely with students to ensure a wide range of initiatives and activities for engaging them throughout the academic year.\n\n=== '''HEALTH AND MEDICAL SERVICES''' ===\nThe University provides the students a well-equipped [[First aid|first-aid]] support in the [[Hospital|Infirmary]], It\u2019s also equipped with [[ambulance]] evacuation for the students. There are two male and two female doctors to provide [[Medical Support Officer|medical support]] to the students. Medical supports, which are beyond the infirmary, facilitated through a high-tech medical ambulance that is present with [[emergency management]] facilities. All the registered students in UPES are medically insured for a sum of INR 100,000. The insurance also covers road accident causality.\n\n=== '''FINANCIAL SUPPORT''' ===\nUPES extends financial support to the registered students on merit and means. At the time of admission, students are offered fee-relaxation based on their Class X and XII marks. It continues further based on marks scored by the students in their semester examination. The university has extended financial support to the students who are unable to pay the tuition fee on account of having lost any of the earning parents after their enrollment in UPES. Fee waiver is extended to [[Uttarakhand]] domicile students. Starting 2020, UPES has introduced a special scheme to promote higher education for girls by extending a 25% scholarship on their tuition fees for the complete program duration. \n\n=== '''REMEDIAL COACHING''' ===\nUnderstanding the importance of supporting the students to overcome their learning difficulties and gain confidence and interest in learning, remedial classes are planned and organised each year. The [[remedial education|remedial]] classes are conducted for the students whose performance is not up to the mark, i.e., for the students who secure less than 40% marks in Mid-Term Examination. These classes help the slow learners to fill the gaps in the teaching learning process which may be due to their slow learning pace, lack of understanding, lack of motivation to practice the problems etc. and ultimately enhance their learnings and skills, resulting in [[improvement]] in their [[performance]].\n\n=== SPORTS ACTIVITIES ===\nAt UPES, students are encouraged to focus on physical fitness and sports. Students participate and excel in a variety of games and sports that are organised at regular intervals in the university \u2013 UPES Annual Athletics Meet, Intra Mural Tournaments (All Sports), Inter-University Participation, Yoga and Meditation and Khel Utsav \u2013 UPES Sports Festival.\n\n=== CULTURAL ACTIVITIES ===\nThe cultural committee provides numerous opportunities for students to get involved, have fun, showcase their talents, and compete against other colleges in a variety of competitions. UPES under the aegis of Office of Student Engagement and Experience organises Freshers\u2019 Party and the '''Annual Cultural Festival \u2013 Uurja,'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upes.uurja/|title=Uurja (@upes.uurja) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> '''which gives a platform to students to showcase their talents.''' Freshers\u2019 parties, to officially welcome the first-year students, are hosted by second-year students, organised by School Cultural Convener under the supervision of the office of Student Engagement and Experience. Uurja is the annual cultural festival and is celebrated for two days at UPES Campus. Wow Wednesdays is a mid-week activity that allows students to unwind. This is planned to break the monotonous routine by providing students a platform to showcase their talent.\n\n=== NATIONAL SERVICE SCHEME ===\nThe [[National Service Scheme]] (NSS) has been in operation in UPES since April 2018. The fundamental objective of the NSS is to awaken and enrich the social consciousness of students. The scheme provides an opportunity for students to engage in constructive social action, programs, develop co-operative team spirit and gain skills in democratic leadership quality.\n\nStudent of UPES are the primary beneficiary of the program by way of development of their perception about the community, their skill in performing specific jobs, and in developing the qualities of a leader, an organiser, and an administrator and the overall development of their personality as a whole. Through NSS, they get opportunities to see the community closely and thus get an experience of human nature in relation to their environment. This is how the NSS program aims to make the NSS student youth better citizens through \u2018Development of their Personality through Community Service\u2019. Caring for the environment and people around is fundamental to all activities at UPES. University has adopted several schools in villages and suburbs to impart primary and higher education and computer literacy. Students continuously participate in [[Plantation|tree plantation]] drives, [[donation]] drives, [[rainwater harvesting]], [[Swachh Bharat Mission|Swachh Bharat Abhiyaan]], and [[Women's empowerment|Women\u2019s Empowerment]].\n\n== Innovation & Entrepreneurship ==\n\n=== UPES CENTRE FOR INNOVATION AND ENTREPRENEURSHIP<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/ucie|title=UPES Centre For Innovation and Entrepreneurship (UCIE)|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ===\nThe UPES Centre for Innovation and Entrepreneurship (UCIE) is a Business Incubator (BI) with focus on the technology sectors in [[National Capital Region (India)|Delhi NCR]] and [[Uttarakhand]] region belt. The mandate of the Centre is to assist the UPES community entrepreneurs (faculty, staff, alumni and students) as well as the external community entrepreneurs, commercialise their product/service ideas and/or accelerate their growth. The mission is to synchronize and synergize the interactions between various stakeholders of [[Entrepreneurship]] [[Ecosystem]] with utmost importance on enabling young students to become successful. The key technology focus areas are: [[Transport|Transportation]], [[Infrastructure]], [[E-commerce]], [[Education]], [[Energy]], [[Information technology|IT]]/ITES Gaming and [[Animation]], [[Cloud computing|Cloud Computing]], [[Biotechnology]], [[Energy technology|Energy Technology]], [[Food Processing Technology Building|Food Processing Technology]], Retail Technology and [[Fashion design|Fashion Technology.]] \n\nUCIE believes in providing a platform to enthusiastic, zealous, and aspiring entrepreneurs and in bringing a positive change in the industry with launch of new and promising businesses. It encourages talent and innovative thinking and provides opportunities to the potential change makers of the industry, thereby contributing towards bringing about a positive change. UCIE supports technology start-ups as well as lab-stage innovations and paves the path for potential business ideas to reach the market.\n\n=== '''UCIE ASSOCIATION WITH UNIVERSITY BUSINESS INCUBATOR (UBI) GLOBAL''' ===\nUCIE is a member of UBI Global, this provides the centre a unique opportunity to understand, explore and visualize the state and impact of India's incubation ecosystem in a more efficient way. This also helps in sharing global incubation best practices and insights and nurtures a network within Centre\u2019s own ecosystem. UCIE primarily works with focus on following three parameters and their sub-constituents to improve and evaluate operational and strategic effectiveness.\n\n=== '''UCIE PARTNERS''' ===\nUCIE aims to build an Entrepreneurial ecosystem in [[Uttarakhand]] to strengthen the existing stakeholders by providing them a network to share/discuss/leverage areas of common interest. This would invariably result in valuable help in a short period of time there by economic cooperation in the future. UCIE conducts a series of events with network of local community, Departments of State Government, [[Non-governmental organization|NGOs]], [[Confederation of Indian Industry]] (CII), [[Federation of Indian Chambers of Commerce & Industry]] (FICCI), PHD Chamber of Commerce by providing information about UCIE and its activities to build mutually enriching cooperation and growth of entrepreneurship in Uttarakhand region. This Entrepreneurial ecosystem will also establish contacts with other programs supporting business, data bases, foreign investors and export opportunities.\n\nThe university helps innovative start-ups with incubation services like Networking Activities, Marketing Help, Training for Developing Presentation Skills, Links to Strategic Partners, Expert Advice, Broad Business Training Programs, and more. The workshops developed by the Centre are framed around businesses and involve academic researchers and professionals from the industry. The workshops are organized to provide a basic understanding of what it takes to commercialize and gain various types of business knowledge. Supported by the faculty of UPES and industry experts, these workshops cover a wide variety of topics viz. industry analysis, technical feasibility study, market feasibility, demand forecasting, financial feasibility study, and strategy development. The theoretical knowledge is enhanced by the industry experts and entrepreneurs who also share their personal experiences with the candidates.\n\n== CSR Initiatives at UPES ==\n\n==== '''Project Abhilasha''' ====\nChildren are often deprived of education due to inequalities that emanate from socio-economic status, gender and cultural identities. The idea behind this project is to identify meritorious students from the marginalized regions of the state and invite them for a month-long residential coaching camp on the campus. The focus is on strengthening their grasp of subjects such as Physics, Chemistry, and Maths, thereby making them ready for engineering entrance exams.\n\n==== '''Project Vikalp''' ====\nRural Women Technology Park has been involved in empowerment activities for the women of neighbouring villages surrounding the university campus since 2015. The project supports initiatives related to recycled paper products; ICT-assisted art and craft design; and identification and cultivation of medicinal and aromatic plant species. Additionally, these budding entrepreneurs receive assistance from experts on the campus for the marketing of their products.\n\n==== '''Project Payal''' ====\nProviding education for girls is, arguably, one of the best development investments an organization can make. And that is precisely what Project Payal has set out to achieve. Supporting underprivileged meritorious girls from neighbouring villages, the project makes sure there is an overall development in their personality.\n\n==== '''Project Uthaan''' ====\nSmart Village is fast becoming a buzzword in policy and rural development discussions. This project aims to transform Dhalani and Koti into model smart villages, with special focus on healthcare, education and livelihood. These will be first of many villages to reap the benefits of this program, bringing more development and prosperity to the Indian rural landscape.\n\n==== '''Project Vriddhi''' ====\nEvery child deserves to reach her or his full potential. And education is one of the best predictors of success in children. It can help break the inter-generational cycles of poverty and marginalization. This project aims to provide the desired level of education in English and Mathematics to primary school students. It is helmed by the UPES faculty as mentors and supported by student volunteers.\n\n==== '''Project Samvedna''' ====\nConstruction projects are a tall order and usually require people with varied skill sets to execute it. Workers are typically hired to spend months or even years on any one project. At our campus, too, there are numerous construction projects, thus making it a transit home for\n\nhundreds of workers. This project is aimed at the children of these workers. It provides them with education, day-care, mid-day meals, medical checkups, clothing, etc., through a day school set-up at the campuses.\n\n==== '''Project Bodh''' ====\nEveryone sees the world through their own prism. This project recognizes the fact that all children have their own perception of the world. These are images that are strongly shaped by their individual imagination and experiences. On the occasion of the World Book Day, five students from government primary schools, along with their teachers and principals, participated in a painting competition on the theme of \u2018environment\u2019. The winners took home trophies, while all participants got a bag, books and stationery as gifts.\n\n==== '''Shaheed Memorial Cricket Tournament''' ====\nThe Annual T-20 Shaheed Memorial Cricket Tournament is a way to pay homage to the brave soldiers who laid down their lives for the nation. The 2019 Tournament was organized in the memory of Vir Chakra (Posthumous) Awardee Naik Brij Mohan Singh from 9 Para (SF), a young soldier from Village Tunwala in Dehradun who went down fighting during the Kargil War on July 1, 1999.\n\n==== '''Project Protsaahan''' ====\nOne of the biggest reasons students drop out of college is because of lack of funds to keep going. This project supports meritorious underprivileged students of PYDS Academy of Learning, Purukul \u2013 Dehradun, for their higher education beyond Class XII. It admits two students annually from PYDS \u2013 one boy and one girl \u2013 who qualify the UPES Entrance Examination, into any of its programs and gives annual cumulative academic scholarship of Rs.20 lakh.\n\n==== '''Project Swachhta''' ====\nAligned with the objectives of Swachh Bharat Mission to clean up streets, roads and public spaces in the cities, towns, urban and rural areas, Project Swachhta has evoked a sense of responsibility among the residents of Dehradun too. Cleanliness drives are being conducted at regular interval in areas adjoining the campus. The local residents have also been sensitized to join the program. The aim is to instill the value of cleanliness among youth through voluntary work in order to take the cleanliness drive to the next level.\n\n==== '''Project Samarth''' ====\nTechnology is shaping today\u2019s students and their learning. Hence it is imperative to arm them with a set of competencies that allows them to function and participate fully in a digital world. Project Samarth was envisioned with the sole purpose of providing technological support to the Shrimad Dayanand Arsh Jyotirmath, Gurukul. It equips their students with IT skills, covering their computer studies syllabus and imparting basic computer operational skills to their teachers.\n\n==== '''Project Raftaar''' ====\nWhile academics play a significant role, extra-curricular activities are also important in shaping the personality and character of a student. Children who dabble in these activities are known to display a heightened sense of discipline, concentration, and time-management. Project Raftaar aims at personality development of students in eight government primary schools through sports and cultural activities. An annual inter-school competition with over 300 participants, the event provides the students a platform to compete amongst themselves. \n\n==See also==\n* [[University of Technology and Management]]\n* [[Indian Institute of Technology Roorkee]]\n* [[List of universities in India]]\n* [[List of business schools in Asia]]\n* [[University Grants Commission (India)]]\n\n==References==\nEligibility, Application Form, Admit Card Etc.<ref>[https://university.careers360.com/articles/upes-admission UPES Admission Process]</ref>\nHow to Apply for UPES application Form<ref>[https://university.careers360.com/articles/upes-application-form UPES Application Form Procedure]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{official}}\n\n{{Dehradun}}\n{{Universities in Uttarakhand}}\n{{Colleges Under HERS}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:University of Petroleum and Energy Studies}}\n[[Category:Universities in Uttarakhand]]\n[[Category:Law schools in India]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Dehradun]]\n[[Category:Science and technology in Dehradun]]\n[[Category:Petroleum engineering schools]]\n[[Category:Institutions of Petroleum in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian University}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2017}}\n{{Primary sources|date=March 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox university\n|name           = University of Petroleum & Energy Studies (UPES) \n|image_name     = \n|motto          = \n|mottoeng       = University with a purpose\n|established    = 2003\n|chancellor     = Dr. S J Chopra\n|vice_chancellor= Dr. Sunil Rai\n|undergrad      = \n|city           = [[Bidholi]], Via Prem Nagar, [[Dehradun]]\n|state          = [[Uttarakhand]]\n|country        = India\n|students       =\n|free_label     = \n|free           = \n|type           = Private University<ref name=\"upes.ac.in\">{{cite web|url=http://www.upes.ac.in/accreditations-recognitions|title=Accreditations & Recognitions|website=www.upes.ac.in |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131119091256/http://www.upes.ac.in/accreditations-recognitions |archivedate=19 November 2013 }}</ref>\n|campus         = [[Suburb]]an,{{convert|42|acre|ft2}}\n|affiliations   = [[University Grants Commission (India)|UGC]], [[National Assessment and Accreditation Council|NAAC]], [[Department of Scientific and Industrial Research (India)|DSIR]], [[IGNOU]], [[Association of Indian Universities|AIU]], [[International Association of Universities|IAU]], [[Bar Council of India|BCI]]<ref name=\"upes.ac.in\"/>\n|website        = {{URL|http://www.upes.ac.in/}}\n|coor           ={{Coord|30|24|57.38|N|77|58|1.24|E|display=inline, title}}\n|logo= \n}}\nThe '''[[University of Petroleum and Energy Studies]]''' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/|title=UPES University in Dehradun For Admission in MBA, LLB, B.tech, M.tech|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>'''([https://www.upes.ac.in/ UPES]'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/|title=UPES University in Dehradun For Admission in MBA, LLB, B.tech, M.tech|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>''')''' was established in 2003 through the UPES Act, 2003, of the State Legislature of Uttarakhand. The University is sponsored by Hydrocarbon Education Research Society (HERS) which is a Society registered under the \u201cSocieties Registration Act XXI of 1860\u201d (Registration No. S-41894 of 2002). UPES is maintained by University Grants Commission (UGC) under Section 2(f) of the UGC Act, 1956.\u00a0 The University functions under the ambit of its Act, Statutes, Rules and Regulations.\u00a0 It has also ensured due internal compliance to its obligations towards RTI, Anti Ragging, CSR and other regulations framed by the statutory authorities from time to time.\n\n\nUPES is a UGC-recognized university and has received a 5-star rating for both employability (placements) and campus facilities and a 4-star rating for teaching by the internationally acclaimed QS Ratings. UPES enables its students to achieve their individual purpose in life, through the guiding light of knowledge. UPES offers industry-aligned and specialised graduate and postgraduate programs through its eight schools, viz., School of Engineering<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-engineering|title=School of Engineering : Best School For Engineering in India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>, School of Computer Science<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-computer-science|title=School of Computer Science {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>, School of Design<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-design|title=School of Design : Best Design University in Dehradun, India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>, School of Law<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-law|title=Law School: Best Law University For Legal Studies in India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>, School of Business<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-business|title=School of Business Management : Business School For MBA & Economics - UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>, School of Health Sciences<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-health-sciences|title=School Of Health Sciences - Health Science Course Info {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>, School of Smart Agriculture<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-smart-agriculture|title=School of Smart Agriculture {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref> and School of Modern Media<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-modern-media|title=School of Modern Media {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>. Given its industry-oriented programs and emphasis on holistic development, UPES graduates are the preferred choices for recruiters, which has led to a placement track record of over 90% in the past few years. The university\u2019s core philosophy and purpose of sending outstanding and industry-ready students into the world is its driving force. \n\nUPES has declared 2020 as the Year of Women\u2019s Empowerment. The university, under its '''[https://upesforshakti.upes.ac.in/ \u2018Shakti\u2019]''' initiative, offers 25% scholarship on tuition fees for all girl students for the complete program duration. Beyond offering all girls students a 25% scholarship in year 2020, UPES has been working tremendously towards empowering women of all age groups through its CSR wing. It has undertaken several initiatives that facilitate women to focus on their development through formal education, skill training, and personality grooming. \n\nUPES School of Engineering<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-engineering|title=School of Engineering : Best School For Engineering in India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref> is at the forefront of delivering education that makes sure students are job ready as they graduate. Through the university\u2019s '''[https://www.upes.ac.in/engineering-plus Engineering Plus]''' offering, B.Tech students at UPES can pursue additional specialisations in latest technologies such as artificial intelligence, machine learning, IoT, data analytics and blockchain. A fundamental knowledge of these subjects is essential for today\u2019s engineer as the use of these technologies has become omnipresent in the modern era. UPES School of Engineering also initiated a Diploma in Business Management program for its undergraduate students. This course can be undertaken by the interested students along with their B. Tech program. This would equip students with basic management skills, global perspective towards things, enhance their problem-solving and decision-making skills, thus making them holistic engineers.\n\nIn order to bridge the gap between industry and university, UPES collaborated with '''[[Coursera]]''' which provides a transformative learning experience, through interactive sessions and self-paced modules, that empowers development and ensures graduates are highly employable in an ever-changing world. UPES students have free access to over 3800 global courses and can choose from 190 world\u2019s renowned universities and industry partners such as [[Google]], [[IBM]], [[Boston Consulting Group|BCG]], [[Amazon (company)|Amazon]] [[Web service|Web Services]], etc.\n\nWith a primary focus on life-long learning and knowledge beyond classrooms, UPES believes in giving its students '''global exposure''' and an edge over other students. It has partnered with leading institutions in six countries to provide students with global expertise. UPES graduate students get 50% waiver on PG programs tuition fees in over 22 UPES partner institutions in [[London]], [[Berlin]], [[Canada]] ([[Vancouver]] or [[Toronto]]), [[Singapore]] and [[Dublin]]. Another exciting added advantage is that all UPES students enrolling in the year 2020 can study overseas for four weeks in partner institutions, without any additional tuition fee. The 4-week study abroad program is to give students exposure to global experts, culture, and situations. Students stand to benefit from lectures and seminars by expert faculty, notable guest speakers connected to industry and leading professional practitioners in their field, practical group work and exercises fostering inspiration through participation and making and visits to relevant industry and design studios. \n\nMoreover, UPES is the only university to roll out a plethora of offerings for building life-long connections with its alumni. Under its '''UCONNECT''' program, all alumni get placement support for up to five years, post their graduation from UPES. Support also comes in the form of incubation and funding up to Rs.10 lakh and workspace support in key cities. Alumni also have the advantage of a 35 per cent scholarship on tuition fees for post-graduation at academic partner institutes abroad.\n\n<br />\n\n== Location ==\nUPES is situated in the safe and scenic environs of [[Dehradun]], the capital of the state of [[Uttarakhand]], [[India]]. The sprawling 44-acre University is divided into two campuses \u2013 UPES Bidholi, known as Energy Acres<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://52.5.173.125/|title=UPES University in Dehradun For Admission in MBA, LLB, B.tech, M.tech|website=52.5.173.125|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> and UPES Kandoli, known as Knowledge Acres<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://52.5.173.125/|title=UPES University in Dehradun For Admission in MBA, LLB, B.tech, M.tech|website=52.5.173.125|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>. \n\nThe mountains and the fresh air make UPES a serene abode with a positive atmosphere and a nurturing environment that is essential for the overall development of students. The University has the best infrastructure and is one of the most beautiful campuses in India\n\n==Schools==\n\n=== '''1) School of Health Sciences'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-health-sciences|title=School Of Health Sciences - Health Science Course Info {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> ===\nThe UPES School of Health Sciences focuses on outcome-based education to develop professionals who can meet the healthcare needs of India and beyond. It offers programs in [[Food]], [[Nutrition]] and [[Dietitian|Dietetics]], [[Microbiology]], [[Hospital]] and [[Health administration|Healthcare Management]], [[Pharmacy]] and [[Clinical research|Clinical Research.]] \n\nThe School equips students to serve the growing health needs of the world by becoming specialist health sciences professionals.\n<br />\n\n=== '''2) School of Smart Agriculture'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-smart-agriculture|title=School of Smart Agriculture {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> ===\nStudents of the UPES School of Smart Agriculture get access to latest technologies ranging from the [[Internet of things|Internet of Things]] to [[Big data|Big Data]], [[Artificial intelligence|AI Sensors]] to [[Unmanned aerial vehicle|Unmanned Aerial Vehicles]] and [[Global Positioning System|GPS]] [[Robotics]]. The School offers courses in [[Agriculture]], [[Food technology|Food Technology]] and [[Agronomy]]. \n\nThe syllabus is as per the [[ICAR]] guidelines and Convergence of Tech with Agriculture.\n<br />\n\n=== '''3) School of Modern Media''' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-modern-media|title=School of Modern Media {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> ===\nThe UPES School of Modern Media extends a sturdy platform with state-of-the-art labs, [[Production control room|Production Control Room]] (PCR), Audio Recording Studio, Editing Lab, [[Photography|Photography Lab]] for the students to make a mark on the global media environment. \u00a0\n\nSpecialised programs are offered in [[Journalism]] and [[Mass communication|Mass Communication]], Digital and [[Mass media|Mass Media]], [[Advertising]] and [[Digital marketing|Digital Marketing,]] [[Events]], PR and [[Corporate communication|Corporate Communications]], [[Media]] and [[Entertainment]] and [[Photography]].\n<br />\n\n=== 4) '''School of Law''' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-law|title=Law School: Best Law University For Legal Studies in India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> ===\nThe UPES School of Law equips students with new patterns of practice and innovative tools of management. Students are able to develop alternative routes around regulatory rules that might restrain growth and competition and find resourceful methods to cope with the increasing costs of practice and overheads. \u00a0The School offers programs ranging from [[Energy law|Energy law,]] [[International economic law|International Economic Law]] to [[Constitutional law|Constitutional Law]] and Legal Compliance and Secretarial Practice. \n<br />\n\n=== '''5) School of Engineering''' ===\nThe UPES School of Engineering provides a new type of learning that is engineered to react to the evolving needs and demands of the world, using a combination of technology and human power. It offers courses in the [[Aerospace engineering|Department of Aerospace Engineering,]] [[Applied science|Applied Sciences]], [[Chemical Engineering Science|Chemical Engineering]], [[HSE]] and [[Civil engineering|Civil Engineering]], [[Electrical engineering|Electrical and Electronics Engineering]], [[Mechanical engineering|Mechanical Engineering]] and [[Petroleum engineering|Petroleum Engineering]] and [[Earth science|Earth Sciences.]] \n\n==== '''Additional Specializations with \u2018Engineering Plus'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/engineering-plus|title=Engineering Plus {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>'''\u2019:''' ====\nThe School of Engineering provides additional specialization programs in latest technologies, namely [[Artificial intelligence|Artificial Intelligence]], [[Robotics]] and Self Driven Vehicle, [[Internet of things|Internet of Things]], [[Data analysis|Data Analytics]] and [[Blockchain]]. A knowledge of these subjects is essential for today's engineer as the use of these technologies has become ubiquitous. \n\nSchool of Engineering students, irrespective of their areas of specialization, will be able to undertake a minor degree in any of these topics along with their B. Tech. degree program. This minor degree will allow students to become more diverse and broaden their skill set, enabling them to adapt and contribute in an era marred by constant disruption, thereby improving their job prospects.\n\nThese courses are not mandatory, but open to all engineering students. Each specialization will have 5 courses of 3 credits each and a project spanning between 3rd and 7th semester. All the courses will be led by the faculty.\n\nAlso,'''School of Engineering''' is\n\n* B.Tech. Chemical Engineering (Refining & Petrochemicals) and B.Tech. Automotive Design Engineering are NBA accredited.\n\n<br />\n\n=== '''6) School of Design''' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-design|title=School of Design : Best Design University in Dehradun, India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> ===\nThe UPES School of Design prepares skilled professionals who have expertise in technology and are fully conversant with two or more areas of importance, further reinforcing the need for specialisation. \n\nPrograms are offered in the areas of Industrial and [[Product design|Product Design,]] Interior and Retail Spaces Design, [[Animation]] and VFX Design, [[Fashion design|Fashion Design]], User Experience and Interaction Design and Communication and [[Media Design School|Media Design.]] \n\n=== '''7) School of Computer Science'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-computer-science|title=School of Computer Science {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> ===\nThe UPES School of Computer Science offers programs with specialisation in [[Blockchain]], [[IT infrastructure|IT Infrastructure]], [[Artificial intelligence|Artificial Intelligence]] and [[Machine learning|Machine Learning]], [[Bank|Banking]], [[Financial services|Financial Services]] and [[Insurance]], and [[Computational sustainability|Computational Sustainability]]. \n\nThe students can choose to become [[Application analyst|Application Analyst]] or [[Developer]], [[Computer security|Cyber Security]] or [[Data analysis|Data Analyst]], [[Database administrator|Database Administrator]], Forensic Computer Analyst, [[Game developer|Game Developer]], Information Systems Manager, IT Consultant, Software Engineer, Systems Analyst, UX Designer, Web Designer or Application Developer. \u00a0\n<br />\n\n=== '''8) School of Business''' ===\nAt UPES School of Business, students are groomed to excel in highly competitive business sectors such as tech and finance industry, amongst others. The School offers programs in Departments including [[Economics]] and [[International business|International Business]], [[Energy management|Energy Management]], [[General management|General Management]] and [[Transportation management system|Transportation Management]]. \n\nAlso, '''School of Business''' is\n\n* NIRF Rank 56\n* '''Ranked No. 1 private institute''' in Uttarakhand*\n* Ranked among top '''15 MBA     institutes''' in North India*\n\n* '''IACBE''' accreditation for '''MBA OG''' and '''MBA LSCM'''\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki>By Outlook-iCare India MBA Ranking 2020\n\n\n== The UPES Edge ==\n<br />\n\n=== '''Global Offerings''' ===\nUPES has forged academic partnerships with colleges abroad in [[Europe]] and [[Canada]], facilitating a four-week study exchange opportunity for all students, and 50% [[scholarship]] on tuition fees for [[Postgraduate education|post-graduation.]] \n\nStudents have been given free access to 3800+ global courses from 190 of the world\u2019s most renowned universities and industry partners such as [[Google]], [[IBM]], [[BCG]], [[Amazon]] Web Services, etc. through collaboration with [[Coursera]]. The online international learning platform Coursera allows UPES students to better prepare for the dynamic job landscape and equip themselves with skills required to thrive in the knowledge economy. \n\nStudents will not only gain access to high impact technical courses like Data in [[Database]], Linux Server Management and Security, Object-Oriented Programming in [[Java]], Service-Oriented Architecture, Software Development Processes and Methodologies but also to some of the most in-demand and popular courses on the platform like Blockchain Basics, Programming for Everybody and AI for Everyone. Besides these, there are specialized courses across disciplines like healthcare - Bacteria and Chronic Infections and business - Fundamentals of Project Planning and Management.\n\nThe engaging learning platform has over 1000+ [[Business]] courses, 700 courses on [[Technology]], 380 [[Data science|Data Science]] courses, 100 [[Health]], 780 [[Social science|Social Sciences]], and 341 [[Arts & Humanities in Higher Education|Arts & Humanities]] courses.\n\nUPES is one of the very few colleges in India with this kind of a tie-up with the world\u2019s leading online learning platform.\n<br />\n\n=== '''UConnect: Alumni Advantage''' ===\nAs graduates of the institution, [[Alumnus|alumni]] play an important role and have a special connection with the university. UPES provides its former students with a wonderful support system. Students can choose from a variety of initiatives that the university offers such as [[placement]] support, [[incubation]] support, [[scholarship]] on higher studies, industry-oriented courses and career services.\u00a0 \n\nFollowing are the UPES initiatives for alumni: Assured career mentoring and placement support for 5 years after their year of graduating from UPES\n\n* Access to mentors and industry networking opportunities\n* Incubation support\n* Business set up support\n* Prototype development\n* Research and Development guidance from subject matter experts at UPES\n* Support in the development of prototype from the concept stage\n* Testing of prototype\n* Demonstration of prototype\n* Patent filing support, if applicable\n* Graduation to go-to-market \n* Go-to-market strategy \n* Workshop on company law and regulatory compliances\n* Workshop on business structure and processes\n* Session on company formation\n* Session on funding requirements\n* Inviting incubation bids\n\n\nAccess to industry-oriented online courses at subsidized prices to help them enhance their skillset. UPES alumni can choose courses from Coursera and other online platforms available for UPES students.\n\nUp to 35% scholarship to pursue a PG program of their choice from international UPES academic partner institutes such as [[University of Law|The University of Law]], [[London College of Creative Media]], [[Webster University]], [[London School of Business and Finance]], [[Toronto School of Management,]] [[University Canada West]], [[University of Applied Sciences Europe|University of Applied Sciences- Europe]], GISMA Business School and many more within the [[Global University Systems|Global University System]] (GUS) network. \n<br />\n\n=== '''Placements''' ===\nWith industry-aligned curriculum, emphasis on holistic development, UPES graduates have been the preferred choice for employers, reflected in its superior track record of over 94% placements year after year. The highest pay package for the year 2020 is \u20b9 44 lakhs p.a. The average pay package in 2019 was \u20b9 4.35 lakhs p.a. \n\nThus, the university develops and hones future leaders for diverse high-growth sectors, both in India and overseas. \n<br />\n== History and Governance ==\nStarted with an interim campus in [[Dehradun]] in August 2003 with 3 courses, 224 students and 15 faculty members, the university has grown with a vision. UPES expanded its offerings from hydrocarbons and allied areas to multidisciplinary areas of [[Energy]][[Information technology|/IT]]/[[Transport|Transportation]] to provide industry aligned education. Today UPES is proud to have two sprawling campuses one at [[Bidholi]] and other at Kandholi offering more than 80 industry aligned courses ([[graduate]]{{dn|date=April 2020}}, [[Postgraduate education|post graduate]] and [[Doctoral program|doctoral programs]]) to approximately 12,000+ students in the high growth sectors like [[Energy]], [[Infrastructure]], [[Transport|Transportation]], [[Information technology|Information Technology]], [[Electronics]], [[Design]], [[Business]], [[Public policy|Public Policy]], [[Legal Studies]], etc. through its constituent schools. The vision of the university is to be an institution of global standing for developing professionally competent talent contributing to nation building.\n\nRecognising UPES\u2019 commitment towards delivering domain focused programs, several organisations of national and international repute have pledged to invest knowledge resources in the university. Not only that, many have established labs and knowledge centres within the campus towards the common goal of industry strengthening through superior manpower. \n\nThe university has been accredited by [[National Board of Accreditation]] ([[National Board of Accreditation|NBA]]) for [https://www.upes.ac.in/course/b-tech-automotive-design-engineering Automotive Design Engineering] and Chemical Engineering<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/course/btech-chemical-engineering-refining-and-petrochemicals|title=B. Tech. Chemical Engineering in Refining and Petrochemicals in India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref> (Specialisation: Refining and Petrochemicals) program. Moreover, UPES Centre for Innovation and Entrepreneurship<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/ucie|title=UPES Centre For Innovation and Entrepreneurship (UCIE)|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref> (UCIE) has been recognised as an [[Business incubator|incubator]] by the [[Government of Uttarakhand]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uk.gov.in/|title=Home: Uttarakhand Government Portal, India|website=uk.gov.in|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n\n\n'''UPES has following Statutory Authorities:'''\n\n# Board of Governors - Highest Regulatory Body to lay down policies, approve Budget/Annual Report, make, amend or repeal Statutes & Rules, etc.\n# Board of Management - Principal Executive Body to approve senior appointments, \ufb01x emoluments of employees, approve infrastructural requirements, prepare annual accounts through Finance Committee, accept donations, enter into contracts, select common seal, make rules, etc.\n# Academic Council - Principal academic body to coordinate and exercise general supervision over the academic policies of the University\n# Finance Committee - Principal \ufb01nancial body to take care of \ufb01nancial matters, prepare annual accounts and \ufb01nancial estimates, etc.\n\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|                    '''BOARD OF GOVERNORS'''\n\n'''UPES'''\n\n'''1st September 2018-31st August 2021'''\n|-\n|                    '''MEMBER SECRETARY'''\n|-\n|                              '''Dr. Sunil Rai'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/messages-from-leader/vice-chanellors-message|title=Dr. Sunil Rai|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\nVice-Chancellor\n\nUniversity of Petroleum & Energy Studies\n\nEnergy Acres,P.O Bidholi Via Prem Nagar\n\nDehradun-248007\n|-\n|                       '''Ms. Nandita Abraham''' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pearlacademy.com/|title=Best College in India for Design & Fashion, Business & Media Courses|website=Pearl Academy|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n\nPresident\n\nPearl Academy\n\nA-21/13, Naraina Industrial Area, Phase II\n\nNear Shadipur Metro Station\n\nNew Delhi-110028\n|-\n|                      '''Mr. Rajat Mukherjee'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.khaitanco.com/people/rajat-mukherjee|title=Rajat Mukherjee - Practices, Education & Recognitions|website=Khaitan & Co|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n\nPartner, Merger  and Acquisition Practice Group\n\nKhaitan& Co.Law Firm, Ashoka Estate, 12th Floor, \n\n24 Brakhamba Road, New Delhi-110001\n|}\n\n== Awards & Recognition  ==\nOver the years, UPES has received several awards and accolades, including:\n\n* Leading university for international student experience at the UniAgents Annual Summit 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uniagents.com/india-event/india-event-2019.php|title=UNIAGENTS ANNUAL SUMMIT 2019|website=www.uniagents.com|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n\n* \u2018Excellence in Open & Distance Education\u2019 award at the World Education Summit 2019\n* Blackboard Catalyst Award for student success for Team Career Services at TLC Asia 2019.\n* 'Best Academic-Industry Interface' by DNA (a leading Indian media house) in 2018\n* \u2018Best Industry-Academia Interface\u2019 at the 12th World Education Summit by Digital Learning & Elets Technomedia Pvt. Ltd. in 2018\n* \u2018Best University for Placements and Employability\u2019 by [[Times Now]] - National Education Excellence Award 2018\n* \u2018Great Place to Study\u2019 as per the Great Indian Institutes 2018 list by [[Forbes India]]\n* Ranked amongst top 30 world\u2019s best universities for Oil, Gas and Petroleum engineering by CEO World Magazine (USA) in 2017\n*[[International Accreditation Council for Business Education]] (IACBE) accredited MBA programmes (2017)\n* \u2018Best Training Institute Award\u2019 for the Port and Shipping Management programme at International SHIPTEK conference held in Dubai in 2016\n* Five stars for employability and campus facilities and four stars for teaching methodologies by globally acclaimed QS Ratings in 2016\n* \u2018University with Best Industry Academic Partnership\u2019 by [[India Today (TV channel)|India Today TV]]-Higher Education Excellence Awards\n* \u2018India\u2019s Best University for Innovation and Value based Education\u2019 by the Corporate Council for Leadership & Awareness (CCLA)\n\n== Life at UPES ==\n\n=== '''Student Chapter at UPES''' ===\nStudent Chapters provide unique opportunities for networking, mentoring and bonding over common interests. They provide support both within the student community and to local communities outside the institution. Student Chapters are intended to provide a platform through which students may share their special concerns and run programs for students and other members of the community with an interest in information science.\n\nUnder the '''School of Engineering'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-engineering|title=School of Engineering : Best School For Engineering in India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>, the student chapters are-\n\n* ASHRAE<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/ashraeupes/|title=ASHRAE UPES (@ashraeupes) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[American Society of Heating, Refrigerating and Air Conditioning Engineers|American Society of Heating, Refrigerating and Air-Conditioning Engineers]])\n* ASME<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upesasme/|title=UPES ASME Student Section (@upesasme) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[American Society of Mechanical Engineers]])\n* IEEE<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upes.ieee/|title=UPES IEEE (@upes.ieee) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers|The Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers]]) - IEEE student branch provides a platform for the students to enhance their leadership qualities and technical skills. It organises the various technical and non-technical activities across every year at UPES. Apart from these activities, IEEE student branch conducts its Technical Fest ELECTRA<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/ieeeelectra/|title=UPES IEEE-eLECTRA (@ieeeelectra) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> under the banner of Electrical and Electronics Engineering Department.\n\n* UPES FIPI Student Chapter <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upes_fipi/|title=UPES FIPI Student Chapter (@upes_fipi) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>(Federation of Indian Petroleum Industry) - Students are provided with a series of events and workshops for better learning in the field of Petroleum & Chemical Engineering. UPES FIPI Student Chapter was the first student chapter to be set up in UPES.\n\n* SPE<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upes_spesc/|title=UPES SPE SC (@upes_spesc) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[Society of Petroleum Engineers]])- SPE stands for Society of Petroleum Engineers. SPE is an international not-for-profit organization that works for the enhancement and development of the entire [[Oil and gas industry in India|Oil and Gas industry]]. It is a platform that connects everyone related to Oil and Gas industry, students and professionals alike. [https://www.instagram.com/upes_spesc/ UPES SPE Student Chapter] was set up in 2009 and has been substantiating the mission of SPE International- to collect, disseminate and exchange technical knowledge pertaining to the Energy sector. The Chapter has more than thousand members and provides light to students not only [[Petroleum]] and [[Earth science|Earth Sciences]] but also from [[Chemical engineering|Chemical Engineering]] and [[Computer science|Computer Science]]s. The Chapter has been bridging the gap between Academia and Industry through various events, conferences, and other activities, at national level, regional level and internationally.\n\n* AAPG<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upesaapg/|title=UPES AAPG Student Chapter (@upesaapg) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[American Association of Petroleum Geologists|American Association of Petroleum Geologist]])- It is one of the eight active AAPG student chapters in India. The annual event \u2018Crust\u2019 comprises guest lectures, workshop and trainings.\n\n* SEG<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upes_seg/|title=UPES SEG Student Chapter (@upes_seg) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[Society of Exploration Geophysicists|Society of Explorations Geophysicists]])- Providing a multitude of opportunities to its members, the society has been serving them with events, information and networking since its inception in 2009. The UPES student chapter is affiliated to the SEG society and has been dedicated to the field of [[Geology]] and education of Exploration [[Geophysics|Geophysicists]].\n\n* IIChE<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/iiche_upes/|title=IIChE UPES Student Chapter (@iiche_upes) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[Indian Institute of Chemical Engineers]])- The primary objective of the Students\u2019 Chapter is to promote among students of [[Chemical engineering|Chemical Engineering]] a feeling of fraternity and brotherhood and to complement the objectives and activities of the institute. The activities of the Students\u2019 Chapter includes lectures, film shows and video shows related to the Chemical Engineering education and profession.\n\n* FSAI (Fire and Security Association of India)- FSAI is a non-profit organisation established in 2002 representing the Fire Protection, Life Safety, Security, Building Automation, Loss Prevention and Risk Management domains.\n\n* ASSP ([[American Society of Safety Professionals|American Society of Safety Professional]])- ASSP student section of UPES is the first student section of ASSP in India. At present it consists of 150 student members. The objective of the section is to promote the advancement of the safety profession and safety education and to foster the professional well-being and development of its members within the campus and community.\n\n* GreenUp- Green up is functioning under the [[Department of Health Safety and Environment]] of University of Petroleum & Energy Studies, Dehradun. Green up is a cause against environmental peril. In UPES, Green Up has always strived for extending various initiations taken by [[Government of India|Indian government]] by organising campaigns and events that commence nationally. Green Up is focuses on mobilising and empowering communities to participate in preserving nature and preventing environmental degradation, thereby improving the quality and maintaining the ingenuity and integrity of nature.\n\n* Aero Club<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/aeroclubupes/|title=AeroClub (@aeroclubupes) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> - The club organises paper plane event, Mayday, [[water rocket]] and other events like Aerokriti. In Aerokriti, winners get value certificates and all the participants receive participation certificates. The club releases \u2018Aerogram\u2019- the official college magazine. Aerogram writes out all the achievements, space calendar, space facts of a month and releases by the end of every month.\n\n* Infinity Space Club<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/infinity_space_club/|title=InfinitySpaceClub (@infinity_space_club) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> (ISC) is a student club that functions under Department of [[Aerospace engineering|Aerospace Engineering]], University of Petroleum and Energy Studies. The ISC is a student activity club, which aims at providing technical knowledge to all of its members through a series of workshops, observation nights and guest lectures. Events are conducted regularly which aim at analyzing the current trends in [[Space technology|Space Technology]].\n\n* ASCE<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/asce.upes/|title=ASCE UPES (@asce.upes) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> - [[American Society of Civil Engineers]]\n* UPES-AEE<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upes.aee/|title=UPES - AEE (@upes.aee) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[Association of Energy Engineers]])- This is the newest Student Chapter in UPES.\n\n\nUnder the '''School of Computer Science'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-computer-science|title=School of Computer Science {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>, the student chapters are-\n\n* CSA<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upescsa/|title=UPES CSA (@upescsa) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[Cloud Security Alliance]]) - Cloud is the future technology of Computer Science which is growing at a fast pace. It resolves the storage as well as computational power problems of every individual and hence is being adopted in every domain. Despite all this, the primary obstacle faced by cloud is the security issue. People all around the globe do not consider it to be secure. This society works to eradicate this problem in collaboration with \u2018Cloud Security Alliance\u2019 which is not only an international chapter, but also an international organisation dealing with cloud security and its functionality. This chapter educates the students of UPES about cloud.\n* CSI<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upescsi/|title=UPES CSI STUDENT CHAPTER (@upescsi) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ([[Computer Society of India]]) ISSA Dehradun Chapter- With the burning desire and enthusiasm to be different from the crowd, UPES-CSI Student Chapter was established in the year 2010 and is one of the most active chapters of UPES. The Society focuses on scientific and educational programs directed towards the development of theory and practice of [[Computer science|Computer Science and Technology]]. The Chapter organizes several technical and fun events, seminars, conferences, regional as well as national student conventions. The chapter strives to create a quintessential example of an ideal workplace by evoking participation of 600+ members in its annual national convention \u2013 YUGMAK. Along with various technical and non-technical competitions, UPES-CSI as a student chapter also carries out its duties towards the society through various CSR activities organised every year.\n* UPES ACM<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upesacm/|title=UPES ACM Student Chapter (@upesacm) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> - [[Association for Computing Machinery]]- International chapter based out of [[New York City|New York]]-[[United States|USA]], with the focus to sensitise students in the area of basic computing.\n* [[CodeChef|UPES-CODE CHEF]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/codechefupes/|title=Codechef UPES Campus Chapter (@codechefupes) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n* Smart Analyzers<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/smartanalyzers/|title=Smart Analyzers (@smartanalyzers) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n* HYPERVISION<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upeshypervision/|title=UPES Hypervision (@upeshypervision) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> Informatics Club\n* Cyber Sentinel<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/cybersentinelupes/|title=Cyber Sentinel (@cybersentinelupes) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n\n\nUnder the '''School of Design'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-design|title=School of Design : Best Design University in Dehradun, India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>, the student chapters are-\n\n* Sketching Club\n* UWUTAKU<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/teamuwutaku/|title=UWUTAKU (@teamuwutaku) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n* Film Club\n\n\nUnder the '''School of Business'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-business|title=School of Business Management : Business School For MBA & Economics - UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>, the student chapters are-\n\n* International Affairs    \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0\n* Events\n* Academic & Research \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0      \u00a0\n* E-CELL<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upesecell/|title=Entrepreneurship Cell - UPES (@upesecell) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n* Corporate Relations \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0\n* Alumni Relations\n\nUnder the '''School of Law'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/schools/school-of-law|title=Law School: Best Law University For Legal Studies in India {{!}} UPES|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>, the student chapters are-\n\n* Society of Law and Literature (SOLL)\n* Moot Court Association<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upes.mca/|title=UPES Moot Court Association (@upes.mca) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n* Technolawgy Society\n* ADR Association<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upes_lac_adr_/|title=LAC ADR Association UPES (@upes_lac_adr_) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n* UCost IPR Cell<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upes_ucost_iprcell/|title=Upes-Ucost IPR CELL (@upes_ucost_iprcell) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n\n=== '''PERSONAL COUNSELING''' ===\nUPES has a well-developed team of professionals offering empathetic hands to lift students out of the pit of ambiguities, disappointments, confusion, and depression. A full-time psychological [[School counselor|counselor]] adopts a holistic approach and includes all domains of student\u2019s life while providing group and one to one counseling. Difficulties in academics and learning are dealt with through faculty mentors. UPES is among one of the few universities that understand the student's need for a friend, guide, role model and mentor. The department of Student Engagement and Experience works closely with students to ensure a wide range of initiatives and activities for engaging them throughout the academic year.\n\n=== '''HEALTH AND MEDICAL SERVICES''' ===\nThe University provides the students a well-equipped [[First aid|first-aid]] support in the [[Hospital|Infirmary]], It\u2019s also equipped with [[ambulance]] evacuation for the students. There are two male and two female doctors to provide [[Medical Support Officer|medical support]] to the students. Medical supports, which are beyond the infirmary, facilitated through a high-tech medical ambulance that is present with [[emergency management]] facilities. All the registered students in UPES are medically insured for a sum of INR 100,000. The insurance also covers road accident causality.\n\n=== '''FINANCIAL SUPPORT''' ===\nUPES extends financial support to the registered students on merit and means. At the time of admission, students are offered fee-relaxation based on their Class X and XII marks. It continues further based on marks scored by the students in their semester examination. The university has extended financial support to the students who are unable to pay the tuition fee on account of having lost any of the earning parents after their enrollment in UPES. Fee waiver is extended to [[Uttarakhand]] domicile students. Starting 2020, UPES has introduced a special scheme to promote higher education for girls by extending a 25% scholarship on their tuition fees for the complete program duration. \n\n=== '''REMEDIAL COACHING''' ===\nUnderstanding the importance of supporting the students to overcome their learning difficulties and gain confidence and interest in learning, remedial classes are planned and organised each year. The [[remedial education|remedial]] classes are conducted for the students whose performance is not up to the mark, i.e., for the students who secure less than 40% marks in Mid-Term Examination. These classes help the slow learners to fill the gaps in the teaching learning process which may be due to their slow learning pace, lack of understanding, lack of motivation to practice the problems etc. and ultimately enhance their learnings and skills, resulting in [[improvement]] in their [[performance]].\n\n=== SPORTS ACTIVITIES ===\nAt UPES, students are encouraged to focus on physical fitness and sports. Students participate and excel in a variety of games and sports that are organised at regular intervals in the university \u2013 UPES Annual Athletics Meet, Intra Mural Tournaments (All Sports), Inter-University Participation, Yoga and Meditation and Khel Utsav \u2013 UPES Sports Festival.\n\n=== CULTURAL ACTIVITIES ===\nThe cultural committee provides numerous opportunities for students to get involved, have fun, showcase their talents, and compete against other colleges in a variety of competitions. UPES under the aegis of Office of Student Engagement and Experience organises Freshers\u2019 Party and the '''Annual Cultural Festival \u2013 Uurja,'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/upes.uurja/|title=Uurja (@upes.uurja) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> '''which gives a platform to students to showcase their talents.''' Freshers\u2019 parties, to officially welcome the first-year students, are hosted by second-year students, organised by School Cultural Convener under the supervision of the office of Student Engagement and Experience. Uurja is the annual cultural festival and is celebrated for two days at UPES Campus. Wow Wednesdays is a mid-week activity that allows students to unwind. This is planned to break the monotonous routine by providing students a platform to showcase their talent.\n\n=== NATIONAL SERVICE SCHEME ===\nThe [[National Service Scheme]] (NSS) has been in operation in UPES since April 2018. The fundamental objective of the NSS is to awaken and enrich the social consciousness of students. The scheme provides an opportunity for students to engage in constructive social action, programs, develop co-operative team spirit and gain skills in democratic leadership quality.\n\nStudent of UPES are the primary beneficiary of the program by way of development of their perception about the community, their skill in performing specific jobs, and in developing the qualities of a leader, an organiser, and an administrator and the overall development of their personality as a whole. Through NSS, they get opportunities to see the community closely and thus get an experience of human nature in relation to their environment. This is how the NSS program aims to make the NSS student youth better citizens through \u2018Development of their Personality through Community Service\u2019. Caring for the environment and people around is fundamental to all activities at UPES. University has adopted several schools in villages and suburbs to impart primary and higher education and computer literacy. Students continuously participate in [[Plantation|tree plantation]] drives, [[donation]] drives, [[rainwater harvesting]], [[Swachh Bharat Mission|Swachh Bharat Abhiyaan]], and [[Women's empowerment|Women\u2019s Empowerment]].\n\n== Innovation & Entrepreneurship ==\n\n=== UPES CENTRE FOR INNOVATION AND ENTREPRENEURSHIP<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.upes.ac.in/ucie|title=UPES Centre For Innovation and Entrepreneurship (UCIE)|website=www.upes.ac.in|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> ===\nThe UPES Centre for Innovation and Entrepreneurship (UCIE) is a Business Incubator (BI) with focus on the technology sectors in [[National Capital Region (India)|Delhi NCR]] and [[Uttarakhand]] region belt. The mandate of the Centre is to assist the UPES community entrepreneurs (faculty, staff, alumni and students) as well as the external community entrepreneurs, commercialise their product/service ideas and/or accelerate their growth. The mission is to synchronize and synergize the interactions between various stakeholders of [[Entrepreneurship]] [[Ecosystem]] with utmost importance on enabling young students to become successful. The key technology focus areas are: [[Transport|Transportation]], [[Infrastructure]], [[E-commerce]], [[Education]], [[Energy]], [[Information technology|IT]]/ITES Gaming and [[Animation]], [[Cloud computing|Cloud Computing]], [[Biotechnology]], [[Energy technology|Energy Technology]], [[Food Processing Technology Building|Food Processing Technology]], Retail Technology and [[Fashion design|Fashion Technology.]] \n\nUCIE believes in providing a platform to enthusiastic, zealous, and aspiring entrepreneurs and in bringing a positive change in the industry with launch of new and promising businesses. It encourages talent and innovative thinking and provides opportunities to the potential change makers of the industry, thereby contributing towards bringing about a positive change. UCIE supports technology start-ups as well as lab-stage innovations and paves the path for potential business ideas to reach the market.\n\n=== '''UCIE ASSOCIATION WITH UNIVERSITY BUSINESS INCUBATOR (UBI) GLOBAL''' ===\nUCIE is a member of UBI Global, this provides the centre a unique opportunity to understand, explore and visualize the state and impact of India's incubation ecosystem in a more efficient way. This also helps in sharing global incubation best practices and insights and nurtures a network within Centre\u2019s own ecosystem. UCIE primarily works with focus on following three parameters and their sub-constituents to improve and evaluate operational and strategic effectiveness.\n\n=== '''UCIE PARTNERS''' ===\nUCIE aims to build an Entrepreneurial ecosystem in [[Uttarakhand]] to strengthen the existing stakeholders by providing them a network to share/discuss/leverage areas of common interest. This would invariably result in valuable help in a short period of time there by economic cooperation in the future. UCIE conducts a series of events with network of local community, Departments of State Government, [[Non-governmental organization|NGOs]], [[Confederation of Indian Industry]] (CII), [[Federation of Indian Chambers of Commerce & Industry]] (FICCI), PHD Chamber of Commerce by providing information about UCIE and its activities to build mutually enriching cooperation and growth of entrepreneurship in Uttarakhand region. This Entrepreneurial ecosystem will also establish contacts with other programs supporting business, data bases, foreign investors and export opportunities.\n\nThe university helps innovative start-ups with incubation services like Networking Activities, Marketing Help, Training for Developing Presentation Skills, Links to Strategic Partners, Expert Advice, Broad Business Training Programs, and more. The workshops developed by the Centre are framed around businesses and involve academic researchers and professionals from the industry. The workshops are organized to provide a basic understanding of what it takes to commercialize and gain various types of business knowledge. Supported by the faculty of UPES and industry experts, these workshops cover a wide variety of topics viz. industry analysis, technical feasibility study, market feasibility, demand forecasting, financial feasibility study, and strategy development. The theoretical knowledge is enhanced by the industry experts and entrepreneurs who also share their personal experiences with the candidates.\n\n== CSR Initiatives at UPES ==\n\n==== '''Project Abhilasha''' ====\nChildren are often deprived of education due to inequalities that emanate from socio-economic status, gender and cultural identities. The idea behind this project is to identify meritorious students from the marginalized regions of the state and invite them for a month-long residential coaching camp on the campus. The focus is on strengthening their grasp of subjects such as Physics, Chemistry, and Maths, thereby making them ready for engineering entrance exams.\n\n==== '''Project Vikalp''' ====\nRural Women Technology Park has been involved in empowerment activities for the women of neighbouring villages surrounding the university campus since 2015. The project supports initiatives related to recycled paper products; ICT-assisted art and craft design; and identification and cultivation of medicinal and aromatic plant species. Additionally, these budding entrepreneurs receive assistance from experts on the campus for the marketing of their products.\n\n==== '''Project Payal''' ====\nProviding education for girls is, arguably, one of the best development investments an organization can make. And that is precisely what Project Payal has set out to achieve. Supporting underprivileged meritorious girls from neighbouring villages, the project makes sure there is an overall development in their personality.\n\n==== '''Project Uthaan''' ====\nSmart Village is fast becoming a buzzword in policy and rural development discussions. This project aims to transform Dhalani and Koti into model smart villages, with special focus on healthcare, education and livelihood. These will be first of many villages to reap the benefits of this program, bringing more development and prosperity to the Indian rural landscape.\n\n==== '''Project Vriddhi''' ====\nEvery child deserves to reach her or his full potential. And education is one of the best predictors of success in children. It can help break the inter-generational cycles of poverty and marginalization. This project aims to provide the desired level of education in English and Mathematics to primary school students. It is helmed by the UPES faculty as mentors and supported by student volunteers.\n\n==== '''Project Samvedna''' ====\nConstruction projects are a tall order and usually require people with varied skill sets to execute it. Workers are typically hired to spend months or even years on any one project. At our campus, too, there are numerous construction projects, thus making it a transit home for\n\nhundreds of workers. This project is aimed at the children of these workers. It provides them with education, day-care, mid-day meals, medical checkups, clothing, etc., through a day school set-up at the campuses.\n\n==== '''Project Bodh''' ====\nEveryone sees the world through their own prism. This project recognizes the fact that all children have their own perception of the world. These are images that are strongly shaped by their individual imagination and experiences. On the occasion of the World Book Day, five students from government primary schools, along with their teachers and principals, participated in a painting competition on the theme of \u2018environment\u2019. The winners took home trophies, while all participants got a bag, books and stationery as gifts.\n\n==== '''Shaheed Memorial Cricket Tournament''' ====\nThe Annual T-20 Shaheed Memorial Cricket Tournament is a way to pay homage to the brave soldiers who laid down their lives for the nation. The 2019 Tournament was organized in the memory of Vir Chakra (Posthumous) Awardee Naik Brij Mohan Singh from 9 Para (SF), a young soldier from Village Tunwala in Dehradun who went down fighting during the Kargil War on July 1, 1999.\n\n==== '''Project Protsaahan''' ====\nOne of the biggest reasons students drop out of college is because of lack of funds to keep going. This project supports meritorious underprivileged students of PYDS Academy of Learning, Purukul \u2013 Dehradun, for their higher education beyond Class XII. It admits two students annually from PYDS \u2013 one boy and one girl \u2013 who qualify the UPES Entrance Examination, into any of its programs and gives annual cumulative academic scholarship of Rs.20 lakh.\n\n==== '''Project Swachhta''' ====\nAligned with the objectives of Swachh Bharat Mission to clean up streets, roads and public spaces in the cities, towns, urban and rural areas, Project Swachhta has evoked a sense of responsibility among the residents of Dehradun too. Cleanliness drives are being conducted at regular interval in areas adjoining the campus. The local residents have also been sensitized to join the program. The aim is to instill the value of cleanliness among youth through voluntary work in order to take the cleanliness drive to the next level.\n\n==== '''Project Samarth''' ====\nTechnology is shaping today\u2019s students and their learning. Hence it is imperative to arm them with a set of competencies that allows them to function and participate fully in a digital world. Project Samarth was envisioned with the sole purpose of providing technological support to the Shrimad Dayanand Arsh Jyotirmath, Gurukul. It equips their students with IT skills, covering their computer studies syllabus and imparting basic computer operational skills to their teachers.\n\n==== '''Project Raftaar''' ====\nWhile academics play a significant role, extra-curricular activities are also important in shaping the personality and character of a student. Children who dabble in these activities are known to display a heightened sense of discipline, concentration, and time-management. Project Raftaar aims at personality development of students in eight government primary schools through sports and cultural activities. An annual inter-school competition with over 300 participants, the event provides the students a platform to compete amongst themselves. \n\n==See also==\n* [[University of Technology and Management]]\n* [[Indian Institute of Technology Roorkee]]\n* [[List of universities in India]]\n* [[List of business schools in Asia]]\n* [[University Grants Commission (India)]]\n\n==References==\nEligibility, Application Form, Admit Card Etc.<ref>[https://university.careers360.com/articles/upes-admission UPES Admission Process]</ref>\nHow to Apply for UPES application Form<ref>[https://university.careers360.com/articles/upes-application-form UPES Application Form Procedure]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{official}}\n\n{{Dehradun}}\n{{Universities in Uttarakhand}}\n{{Colleges Under HERS}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:University of Petroleum and Energy Studies}}\n[[Category:Universities in Uttarakhand]]\n[[Category:Law schools in India]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Dehradun]]\n[[Category:Science and technology in Dehradun]]\n[[Category:Petroleum engineering schools]]\n[[Category:Institutions of Petroleum in India]]\n", "name_user": "BD2412", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200e'''Global Offerings''':Fixing links to disambiguation pages, improving links, other minor cleanup tasks", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Petroleum_and_Energy_Studies"}
